%% Diagram: DNSSEC chain of trust — root anchor down to a signed RRset
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant V as Validating Resolver
    participant R as Root (.)
    participant T as TLD (com)
    participant Z as Zone (example.com)

    Note over V: Pre-configured trust anchor:\nroot KSK public key (RFC 5011)
    V->>R: DNSKEY .
    R-->>V: root DNSKEY + RRSIG (signed by root KSK)
    V->>V: Verify root DNSKEY against trust anchor
    V->>R: DS com.
    R-->>V: DS com. + RRSIG (signed by root ZSK)
    V->>T: DNSKEY com.
    T-->>V: com DNSKEY + RRSIG (signed by com KSK)
    V->>V: Verify com KSK hash matches root's DS for com
    V->>T: DS example.com.
    T-->>V: DS example.com + RRSIG (signed by com ZSK)
    V->>Z: DNSKEY example.com.
    Z-->>V: example.com DNSKEY + RRSIG (signed by zone KSK)
    V->>V: Verify zone KSK hash matches com's DS
    V->>Z: A example.com
    Z-->>V: A RRset + RRSIG (signed by zone ZSK)
    V->>V: Verify A RRset signature with zone ZSK
    Note over V: Chain validated — set AD flag.\nAny break → SERVFAIL + EDE 6 (Bogus)
